                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3269: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 27, 1929—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your 16, February 27, noon. President Leguia will probably discuss cost of
                    new port when he delivers engineers’ report to Ambassador Figueroa. I will
                    telegraph immediately when President Leguia submits it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
